author: Travis Simpson (noreply@couriernews.com)
title: Lady Cyclones fight Greenwood for top seed
text: slideshow ALMA — The Russellville Lady Cyclones volleyball team breezed past the Alma Airdalettes on Tuesday 25-14, 25-18, 25-18.Russellville head coach Cindy Jones said with the Alma win behind them, the Lady Cyclones can begin focusing on today’s Dig Pink game against the Greenwood Lady Bulldogs.The Alma win clinched a spot in the Class 6A state tournament, but seeding will be determined by today’s match against Greenwood.“Thursday night becomes a huge game,” Jones said in a Facebook post on Tuesday. “Not only is it Dig Pink, but it will more than likely determine if we get the No. 1 or No. 2 seed.”Dig Pink is coordinated with hundreds of other events across the nation through the Side-Out Foundation to raise funds for breast cancer research through high school and collegiate girls’ volleyball events.Current statistics indicate 1 in 8 women will develop breast cancer at some point during their lives. Early detection is the key to survival. October is National Breast Cancer Awareness Month.Students, faculty, parents as well as the general public who wear pink to the Cyclones Dig Pink match tonight will gain admission for $1.The Lady Cyclones will wear special pink jerseys.The event raised $3,500 for breast cancer research last year. Junior varsity games will tipoff a 4:30 p.m. with the varsity immediately afterward.
